@NODE GETTING_STARTED "Getting Started"
@PREV INTRODUCTION
@NEXT MAIN_WINDOW
@TOC MAIN

@{APEN 2}@{B}Getting Started@{UB}@{APEN 1}
===============

To get started with iTidy:

1. Double-click the iTidy icon from your Workbench desktop to launch the
   program.

2. In the main window, use the @{B}Browse...@{UB} button to select the folder or
   partition you want to tidy. The selected path will appear in the
   Folder Path display.

3. Choose your preferred sorting order for icons using the @{B}Order@{UB} cycle
   gadget (Folders First, Files First, or Mixed).

4. If you want to tidy all subfolders as well, enable the @{B}Cleanup
   subfolders@{UB} option.

5. For more control over icon layout, window shape, and spacing, click
   @{B}Advanced...@{UB} to open the Advanced Settings window.

6. When ready, click @{B}Start@{UB} to begin tidying. iTidy will process the
   selected folder (and subfolders, if enabled), arranging icons and
   resizing windows according to your chosen settings.

7. If you enabled backups, iTidy will create a restore point before
   making changes. You can revert to this backup later using @{B}Restore
   Backups...@{UB}.

@{B}Tip:@{UB} For your first run, try tidying a small folder to see how the options
affect icon layout and window size. You can always restore from backup if
you want to undo changes.

@{"Back to top" LINK GETTING_STARTED}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------


@{"  Return to Contents  " LINK MAIN}

@ENDNODE

@NODE MAIN_WINDOW "Main Window"
@PREV GETTING_STARTED
@NEXT ADVANCED_SETTINGS
@TOC MAIN

@{APEN 2}@{B}Main Window@{UB}@{APEN 1}
===========

The iTidy main window is designed for fast, easy access to the most
important icon tidying features. Here's a breakdown of each section and
control:


@{APEN 2}FOLDER SECTION@{APEN 1}
--------------

- @{B}Folder Path:@{UB} Displays the Amiga path of the folder to be processed
  (e.g., "SYS:", "Work:Projects", "DH0:Games"). This is read-only and
  updates when you select a new folder.

- @{B}Browse... Button:@{UB} Opens the AmigaDOS file requester, allowing you to
  navigate and select the folder you want to tidy. Only drawers
  (folders) are shown, not files. You can also type a path directly. The
  last selected path is remembered during your session.


@{APEN 2}TIDY OPTIONS SECTION@{APEN 1}
--------------------

- @{B}Order:@{UB} Cycle gadget with options for Folders First, Files First, or
  Mixed. Controls how icons are grouped and sorted in the window.
  - @{I}Folders First:@{UI} All drawer icons appear before file icons.
  - @{I}Files First:@{UI} All file icons appear before drawer icons.
  - @{I}Mixed:@{UI} Folders and files are sorted together alphabetically.

- @{B}Cleanup subfolders:@{UB} When checked, iTidy processes all subdirectories
  within the selected folder tree. Useful for tidying entire partitions
  or large project trees in one pass. @{B}Note:@{UB} On classic hardware this may
  take a while for very large folder trees, but it's safe to let iTidy
  run unattended while it works.

- @{B}Backup icons:@{UB} When checked, iTidy creates an LhA archive backup of all
  ".info" files before making changes. This backs up icon positions and
  window layouts--restored via @{B}Restore Backups...@{UB} in the main window.
  Requires LhA in "C:" directory. Highly recommended for large
  operations. @{B}Note:@{UB} This is separate from Default Tool backups, which
  are handled automatically when fixing default tools.

- @{B}Position:@{UB} Controls where folder windows appear after resizing.
  Options:
  - @{I}Center Screen:@{UI} Window centered on Workbench screen (default).
  - @{I}Keep Position:@{UI} Window stays at current location.
  - @{I}Near Parent:@{UI} Opens slightly down and right of parent window.
  - @{I}No Change:@{UI} Window resized but not moved.


@{APEN 2}OTHER CONTROLS@{APEN 1}
--------------

- @{B}Start Button:@{UB} Begins the tidying process using your current settings.

- @{B}Advanced...:@{UB} Opens the Advanced Settings window for further
  customization.


@{APEN 2}MENU OPTIONS@{APEN 1}
------------

iTidy includes menu options to load and save your current settings:

- @{B}Load Settings:@{UB} Restore previously saved preferences for icon layout,
  sorting, and backup options.
- @{B}Save Settings:@{UB} Store your current configuration for future use, making
  it easy to repeat your preferred setup.

These options help you quickly switch between different layouts or restore
your favorite configuration after experimenting with new settings.


@{APEN 2}TIPS@{APEN 1}
----

- The main window is optimized for quick, one-click tidying. For more
  control, use Advanced Settings.
- You can always return to the main window from other dialogs.
- All changes are applied to the selected folder and, if enabled, its
  subfolders.

@{"Back to top" LINK MAIN_WINDOW}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------


@{"  Return to Contents  " LINK MAIN}

@ENDNODE

@NODE ADVANCED_SETTINGS "Advanced Settings"
@PREV MAIN_WINDOW
@NEXT DEFAULT_TOOL_ANALYSIS
@TOC MAIN

@{APEN 2}@{B}Advanced Settings@{UB}@{APEN 1}
=================

Accessed via @{B}Advanced...@{UB} in the main window. These options give you
fine-grained control over icon layout and window sizing.


@{APEN 2}LAYOUT ASPECT RATIO@{APEN 1}
-------------------

Controls the target width-to-height ratio for folder windows.

- @{I}Tall (0.75):@{UI} Very tall, narrow windows
- @{I}Square (1.0):@{UI} Square windows
- @{I}Compact (1.3):@{UI} Slightly wider than tall
- @{I}Classic (1.6):@{UI} Traditional Workbench proportions
- @{I}Wide (2.0):@{UI} Wide, modern proportions (default)
- @{I}Ultrawide (2.4):@{UI} Very wide windows


@{APEN 2}OVERFLOW STRATEGY@{APEN 1}
-----------------

Determines how iTidy handles folders with too many icons to fit on screen.

- @{I}Expand Horizontally:@{UI} Adds more columns, user scrolls horizontally
  (default)
- @{I}Expand Vertically:@{UI} Adds more rows, user scrolls vertically
- @{I}Expand Both:@{UI} Balances expansion in both directions


@{APEN 2}ICON SPACING (X AND Y)@{APEN 1}
----------------------

Sets the horizontal and vertical gap between icons (0-20 pixels). Default
is 8 pixels for both. Lower values create tighter layouts.


@{APEN 2}ICONS PER ROW (MIN/MAX)@{APEN 1}
-----------------------

- @{B}Min:@{UB} Minimum columns (default: 2). Prevents single-column vertical
  stacks.
- @{B}Max:@{UB} Maximum columns. Only used when Auto Max is disabled.
- @{B}Auto Max Icons:@{UB} When checked (default), iTidy calculates max columns
  automatically based on screen width.


@{APEN 2}MAX WINDOW WIDTH@{APEN 1}
----------------

Limits folder window width as a percentage of screen width (Auto, 30%,
50%, 70%, 90%, 100%). Only applies when Auto Max Icons is enabled.


@{APEN 2}ALIGN ICONS VERTICALLY@{APEN 1}
----------------------

Controls vertical alignment when icons in a row have different heights:
@{I}Top@{UI}, @{I}Middle@{UI} (default), or @{I}Bottom@{UI}.


@{APEN 2}REVERSE SORT (Z->A)@{APEN 1}
-------------------

When checked, reverses the sort order (Z->A, newest-first, largest-first).


@{APEN 2}OPTIMIZE COLUMN WIDTHS@{APEN 1}
----------------------

When checked (default), each column width is based on its widest icon
rather than a uniform width for all columns.


@{APEN 2}COLUMN LAYOUT (CENTERED)@{APEN 1}
------------------------

When checked (default), icons are centered within their column rather than
left-aligned.


@{APEN 2}SKIP HIDDEN FOLDERS@{APEN 1}
-------------------

When checked (default), skips folders without ".info" files during
recursive processing.


@{APEN 2}STRIP NEWICON BORDERS@{APEN 1}
---------------------

Removes borders from NewIcons during processing. Requires icon.library
v44+ (Workbench 3.5+). @{B}Important:@{UB} This change is permanent for the
affected icons, so enable icon backups first if you might want to restore
the original look later.

@{"Back to top" LINK ADVANCED_SETTINGS}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------


@{"  Return to Contents  " LINK MAIN}

@ENDNODE

@NODE DEFAULT_TOOL_ANALYSIS "Default Tool Analysis"
@PREV ADVANCED_SETTINGS
@NEXT RESTORING_BACKUPS
@TOC MAIN

@{APEN 2}@{B}Default Tool Analysis@{UB}@{APEN 1}
=====================

Accessed via @{B}Fix Default Tools...@{UB} in the main window. This feature scans
WBPROJECT icons to find and repair missing or invalid default tools.


@{APEN 2}WHAT IS A DEFAULT TOOL?@{APEN 1}
-----------------------

Every Amiga data file icon specifies a "Default Tool"--the program that
opens when you double-click it. For example, a ".txt" file might use
"SYS:Utilities/MultiView". When icons are copied between systems or
extracted from archives, these tool paths often point to programs that
don't exist, causing "Unable to open your tool" errors.


@{APEN 2}USING THE SCANNER@{APEN 1}
-----------------

1. @{B}Select folder:@{UB} Use @{B}Browse...@{UB} to choose a folder. Scanning is always
   recursive.
2. @{B}Scan:@{UB} Click @{B}Scan@{UB} to examine all icons and check if their default
   tools exist.
3. @{B}Review:@{UB} The tool list shows each default tool, how many icons use it,
   and its status (EXISTS or MISSING).
4. @{B}Filter:@{UB} Use the cycle gadget to show All, Existing only, or Missing
   only.
5. @{B}Fix:@{UB} Select a missing tool and click @{B}Replace Tool (Batch)@{UB} to fix all
   icons using it, or select a specific file and use @{B}Replace Tool
   (Single)@{UB}.


@{APEN 2}TOOL LIST COLUMNS@{APEN 1}
-----------------

- @{B}Tool:@{UB} The default tool path (e.g., "SYS:Tools/TextEdit")
- @{B}Files:@{UB} Number of icons using this tool
- @{B}Status:@{UB} MISSING or EXISTS


@{APEN 2}MENU OPTIONS@{APEN 1}
------------

- @{B}Project menu:@{UB} New, Open, Save, Save As, Close. Saving scans is useful
  for large drives that take time to scan.
- @{B}File menu:@{UB} Export tool list or detailed file list to text files.


@{APEN 2}DEFAULT TOOL BACKUPS@{APEN 1}
--------------------

iTidy automatically backs up original default tool paths (as small text
files) before making changes. This is a separate backup system from the
icon layout backups created during tidying. Use @{B}Restore Default Tools
Backups...@{UB} within this window to revert default tool changes--this does
not restore icon positions or window layouts.


@{APEN 2}TECHNICAL NOTES@{APEN 1}
---------------

iTidy searches the full Amiga PATH (parsed from "S:Startup-Sequence" and
"S:User-Startup") when validating simple tool names like "MultiView".
Absolute paths are checked directly.

@{"Back to top" LINK DEFAULT_TOOL_ANALYSIS}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------


@{"  Return to Contents  " LINK MAIN}

@ENDNODE

@NODE RESTORING_BACKUPS "Restoring Backups"
@PREV DEFAULT_TOOL_ANALYSIS
@NEXT TIPS_TROUBLESHOOTING
@TOC MAIN

@{APEN 2}@{B}Restoring Backups@{UB}@{APEN 1}
=================

Accessed via @{B}Restore Backups...@{UB} in the main window. This feature restores
icon positions and window layouts from iTidy's LhA backup archives. Only
available if you previously ran iTidy with @{B}Backup icons@{UB} enabled.

@{B}Note:@{UB} This restores icon layout backups only. To restore default tool
changes, use @{B}Restore Default Tools Backups...@{UB} in the Fix Default Tools
window instead.


@{APEN 2}RUN LIST@{APEN 1}
--------

The top list shows all previous backup runs:

- @{B}Run:@{UB} Sequential identifier (0001, 0002, etc.)
- @{B}Date/Time:@{UB} When the backup was created
- @{B}Folders:@{UB} Number of folders backed up
- @{B}Size:@{UB} Total archive size
- @{B}Status:@{UB} Complete or Incomplete

Click a run to select it and view details below.


@{APEN 2}DETAILS PANEL@{APEN 1}
-------------

Shows information about the selected run: source directory, total
archives, size, status, and backup location.


@{APEN 2}CONTROLS@{APEN 1}
--------

- @{B}Restore window positions:@{UB} When checked (default), also restores window
  geometry (position and size). A Workbench restart may be required to
  see changes.


@{APEN 2}BUTTONS@{APEN 1}
-------

- @{B}Restore Run:@{UB} Extracts all archived ".info" files back to their
  original locations, restoring icon positions and window geometry.
- @{B}Delete Run:@{UB} Permanently deletes the selected backup. @{B}Important:@{UB} This
  action cannot be undone, so only delete runs you're sure you no longer
  need.
- @{B}View Folders...:@{UB} Shows all folders included in the selected run.
- @{B}Cancel:@{UB} Close without making changes.


@{APEN 2}WHAT GETS RESTORED@{APEN 1}
------------------

- All ".info" files in each folder
- Icon positions (X/Y coordinates)
- Window geometry (if checkbox enabled)
- Folder view mode settings


@{APEN 2}REQUIREMENTS@{APEN 1}
------------

- LhA must be installed in "C:" directory
- Backup archives in "PROGDIR:Backups/"
- Sufficient disk space for extraction

@{"Back to top" LINK RESTORING_BACKUPS}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------


